<sn><md>### Commonly Used Cytokinins

* BAP (6-Benzylamino purine)
* BA (Benzy adenine)
* 2ip (Isopentyl adenine)
* Kinetine (6–furfur aminopurine)
* Zeatin (4–hydroxy 3 methyl trans 2 butinyl aminopurine)
</md></sn><sn><md>### Function of Cytokinins

* Promote `cell division` and delay leaf aging
* Used as a `growth promoter` in **tissue culture**
* Micropropagation
* `Shoot proliferation` in tissue culture
* `Slow the process of senescence` by preventing chlorophyll breakdown in leaves
* In `combination with auxin`, stimulate cell division and differentiation
* Inhibit formation of `lateral roots`
</md></sn><sn><md>### Organogenesis

Cytokinins and auxin together influence organogenesis
* High cytokinin/auxin ratio → formation of shoots
* Low cytokinin/auxin ratio → formation of roots
